AER 1626579 is a spontaneous case, received on 25/Aug/2015 from a physician via company representative 
(source identification number: 5667) and concerns a male patient of unknown age who developed suspicion of 
progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy and progressive dementia while being treated with rituximab 
(Mabthera).
No medical history, past drugs, concurrent conditions and concomitant medications were reported.
On an unknown date, the patient started therapy with rituximab (route, dose, form and frequency not reported) for 
an unknown indication. Later, he experienced suspicion of progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy with 
neurological symptoms. It was reported that the physician assessed the neurological symptoms as symptoms of 
progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy and admitted to neurology department. His current neurological 
problems were described as progressive dementia associated with age. Later, patient probably returned home. As 
