patient is out of reporting physician's reach and the physician does not even remember the patient's name, the 
physician refused to fill out guided questionnaire regarding occurrence of progressive multifocal 
leukoencephalopathy .
At the time of this report, the outcome of progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy and progressive dementia 
was not reported and it was unknown whether the therapy with rituximab was ongoing or not.
The physician assessed the progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy as possibly (probably) related to rituximab 
and the progressive dementia as not related to rituximab.
No further information was provided.
This case was cross referred with AER 1626578 (same reporter).
Additional information was received on 14/Sep/2015. The following information was added to the case: Event 
progressive dementia  was added. Physician denied to fill the guided questionnaire and its reason was updated in 
narrative.